TITLE: Pompeo says Biden's Iran talks ‘squandered’ Middle East stability: ‘Putting us all at risk’
SUMMARY: In a Sunday interview, former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told Fox News that President Biden's approach to the Middle East has been a big step in the wrong direction.

TITLE: Biden DOJ 'legitimizing' attacks on pro-life centers by not prosecuting Kavanaugh home protesters: Sen. Lee
SUMMARY: Sen. Mike Lee said he was not satisfied with the FBI's response to attacks on pro-life centers, as the Biden DOJ has refused to prosecute protesters at Brett Kavanaugh's home.

TITLE: Hillary Clinton suggests transgender debate 'should not be a priority' for Dems
SUMMARY: Hillary Clinton says the Democratic Party should not treat the transgender debate as a priority, saying the Party should focus on winning elections instead.

TITLE: Biden admin explores bussing migrants to US towns hours beyond border
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden and DHS Sec. Alejandro Mayorkas are drafting plans to send busloads of migrants to U.S. towns hours beyond the border, Republican lawmakers say.

TITLE: Republicans mulling run for president not waiting on Trump
SUMMARY: Prominent Republicans looking to launch their own political campaigns are not waiting for Donald Trump to announce his own candidacy ahead of the 2024 election.

TITLE: Potential 2024 GOP presidential field described as ‘an embarrassment of riches’
SUMMARY: A veteran Republican Party strategist and social conservative leader says the potential field of 2024 GOP presidential contenders could end up being the strongest in modern times.

TITLE: Democratic, Republican strategists sound off on Biden's viability ahead of 2024 election
SUMMARY: Republican and Democratic strategists sound off on whether Biden has the ability to represent his party in a positive light and outshine political opposition should he seek a second term in the White House in 2024.

TITLE: House candidate touts record, says Spanberger is 'worst kind of politician' ahead of Virginia GOP primary
SUMMARY: Yesli Vega, a law enforcement officer and a Republican candidate to represent Virginia's 7th Congressional District, says she is the candidate who can defeat Abigail Spanberger in November.

TITLE: Buttigieg says feds have power to force airlines to hire more workers amid travel delays
SUMMARY: Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg said the federal government has the authority to take action against airline companies that do not meet consumer-protection standards.

TITLE: Biden National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan tests positive for COVID-19
SUMMARY: White House National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan has tested positive for the coronavirus but his office says that he has not been in close contact with the president.

TITLE: Biden hops to prove he's not injured after bike mishap
SUMMARY: President Biden hopped while responding to a reporter's question about how he was doing after Saturday evening after falling off his bike earlier in the day.

TITLE: Democrats, Republicans spar over illegal immigration, national security during Southern Border trip
SUMMARY: Republicans and Democrats on a congressional select committee exchanged broadsides during a trip to southern Texas amid the migrant surge at the border.

TITLE: Former President Trump delivers remarks at American Freedom Tour
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump addressed a crowd Saturday at the American Freedom Tour, a "celebration of faith, family, unalienable rights and God-given American freedoms."

TITLE: DHS announces terror bar exemptions for Afghan evacuees who worked for Taliban-era civil service
SUMMARY: DHS this week announced a move to allow Afghan civil servants who worked during the Taliban regime to be exempted from terror-related restrictions.

TITLE: Hillary Clinton rules out another presidential run as Biden, DNC aim to hold off potential candidates
SUMMARY: Hillary Clinton shut down any speculation that she may launch another bid for the presidency, saying that any future campaign would be "out of the question."

TITLE: Katie Britt, Mo Brooks tout America first agenda ahead of GOP primary runoff election in Alabama
SUMMARY: Katie Britt and Mo Brooks are slated to face off in Alabama on Tuesday in a contentious race for the Senate to replace retiring Sen. Richard Shelby.

TITLE: CBP chief says report on Border Patrol agents accused of 'whipping' migrants to come out in coming weeks
SUMMARY: The head of CBP says a report on the probe into the conduct of Border Patrol agents accused of whipping Haitian migrants will come out in the next several weeks.

TITLE: Biden falls off bike on Delaware ride with first lady, says 'I'm good'
SUMMARY: President Biden fell off his bike Saturday when out for a ride in Rehoboth Beach, Del. with First Lady Jill Biden.

TITLE: New Mexico county's election results certified after court order
SUMMARY: Tensions rose in New Mexico on Friday over the security of voting machines between a Republican-leaning county and Democratic state officials.

TITLE: At the southern border: Dozens of migrants detained as Border Patrol contends with the nightly influx
SUMMARY: Fox News Digital witnessed dozens of migrants being taken into custody Thursday night on the southern border as law enforcement grapples with record border crossings.
